<%# Your forms will need to be complex. Your form for a new figure should
dynamically generate checkboxes out of the available landmarks and titles. It
should also have fields for creating a new landmark and/or a new title. The
controller action that catches the POST request sent by submitting this form
should account for this. The same is true of your form for editing a given
figure. Read the tests very carefully to understand how you should set up your
forms. %>

<form action="/figures" method="POST"> 
   
   <label for="figure_name">New Figure Name:</label>
   <input id="figure_name" type="text" name="figure[name]">

   <h3>Create New Landmark and/or Title:</h3>
   <label for="new_landmark">New Figure Title</label>
   <input id="new_landmark" type="text" name="landmark[name]">

   <label for="new_title">New Figure Landmark</label>
   <input id="new_title" type="text" name="title[name]">

   <h4>Existing Figure Landmarks:</h4>

   <% @landmarks.each do |landmark| %>
   <input type="checkbox" id="landmark_<%= landmark.id %>" name="figure[landmark_ids][]" value="<%= landmark.id %>" ><%= landmark.name %>
   <% end %>
   <br>
   <h4>Exisiting Figure Titles:</h4>
   <% @titles.each do |title| %>
   <input type="checkbox" id="title_<%= title.id %>" name="figure[title_ids][]" value="<%= title.id %>"><%= title.name %>
   <% end %>

   <input type="submit" value="Create New Figure">

</form>